        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Brown the chicken",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Season the chicken thighs generously with salt and pepper on both sides. Heat the oil in a wide casserole dish over a medium-high heat.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Brown the chicken, skin-side down, for 5 to 6 minutes until golden and the skin has crisped. Turn and brown the other side for 2 minutes. Remove and set aside.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Build the braise",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Pour off all but a thin film of fat from the casserole. Add the shallots, cut-side down, and cook over a medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes until golden. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute more.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Pour in the cider and let it bubble for 2 minutes, ",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": []
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "reducing",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpe38lbc000148v4cnuhwt0y"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " slightly. Add the stock, mustard, and tarragon stalks. Stir.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Return the chicken, skin-side up, so the skin sits above the liquid. Cover and simmer over a low heat for 35 to 40 minutes until the chicken is cooked through.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Finish the sauce",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Lift out the chicken. Discard the tarragon stalks. If using cream, stir it into the sauce now. Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes until the sauce has a light coating consistency.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Return the chicken to the pot. Scatter over the fresh tarragon leaves and serve with mashed potato or steamed rice.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Lift out the chicken, remove the lid, and simmer the sauce briskly for 5 to 8 minutes to reduce it.",
                "cause": "Too much liquid was used, or the lid was on the whole time without any reduction.",
                "symptom": "The sauce is watery"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Always position chicken skin-side up so it stays above the sauce. The next time, crispen it briefly under the grill for 3 minutes before serving.",
                "cause": "The skin went into the liquid during cooking.",
                "symptom": "The chicken skin is soggy"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Simmer longer to mellow the sharpness. A teaspoon of cream stirred in at the end softens it further.",
                "cause": "The sauce did not reduce enough, or sweet cider was used instead of dry.",
                "symptom": "The cider tastes sharp"
              },
              {
                "fix": "The fresh leaves should go on at the very end, off the heat. Next time reserve all the fresh leaves for the finish.",
                "cause": "It was added too early and cooked through with the braise.",
                "symptom": "The tarragon has lost its brightness"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Chicken with cider is a dish the British borrowed from the French and made their own. Normandy's poulet vallee d'Auge uses cream and calvados; the British version simplifies it into a weeknight supper, using whatever dry cider sits in the fridge. Tarragon travels from the French tradition but has been at home in British cooking long enough to feel native.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 4,
